│ "  // However, if we are vectorizing, we need to construct the vector       │
│ values.\n  // If the value is known to be uniform after vectorization, we   │
│ can just\n  // broadcast the scalar value corresponding to lane zero.       │
│ Otherwise, we\n  // construct the vector values using insertelement         │
│ instructions. Since the\n  // resulting vectors are stored in State, we     │
│ will only generate the\n  // insertelements once.\n  Value *VectorValue =   │
│ nullptr;\n  if (IsUniform) {\n    // For uniform values, we can broadcast   │
│ the scalar value. The broadcast\n    // will be placed appropriately by     │
